Hidden Unit Zoo

This page has visualizations of what each hidden unit "wants to see" in a restricted Boltzmann machine trained on 4.6m GitHub repository names. The columns in the tables below correspond to positions in a 17-character string. Characters with green backgrounds have strongly positive weights (the model likes these - the greener, the better). Characters with red backgrounds have strongly negative weights (the mode doesn't want to see this character in this position). $ is a special padding character - names shorter than 17 characters are right-padded with it.

Along with each table is a list of strings sampled from the model which have the highest affinity for this hidden unit. The number next to each string is the probability of this hidden unit turning on given that string.

Some examples of hidden units with interesting/interpretable functions:

  • vowel/consonant patterns
    • 181: ^[:vowel:][:consonant:][:consonant:]
    • 268: ^[:vowel:][:consonant:][:vowel:]
    • 340: liquid consonant at position 2, followed by vowel
    • More: 4, 74, 81, 122, 174, 252, 300, 308
  • *.github.io and *.github.com URL patterns: 5, 43, 75, 82, 130, 153, 179, 207, 234, 262, 275, 301, 315, 318, 330, 350
    • Some units have tried to memorize multiple positions simultaneously: 96, 109, 286, 323
  • different lengths: 29, 99, 143, 202
  • word delimiters at different positions: 40, 101, 115, 142, 166, 170, 183, 203, 280, 293, 302
    • These typically have strong positive weights on [.-_] at one particular position, and negative weights on those characters for nearby positions
    • some closely related units mandate a word beginning at a particular position, but with less emphasis on a delimeter (allowing for CamelCase names): 105, 117, 106, 148, 201, 232, 246, 256, 320, 335
  • 114: CAPSLOCK unit
  • 175: pothole_case unit
  • 67: project/proyect/product
  • 54: numeral prefix
    • caps + numerals: 197, 295, 196
  • 331: TLA detector

To learn more, check out my blog post here. To see more samples from this model, check out the GitHub repo generator.
